Description: Tools for processing ambient light exposure data collected from
    wrist-worn actigraphy devices (Axivity AX3/AX6 and ActTrust) in the
    context of circadian and chronobiology research. luxR provides a
    pipeline for photic exposure metrics (mean/median illuminance, time
    above threshold, cumulative photic history, melanopic EDI
    approximation) and light timing and regularity metrics (light
    onset/offset detection, mean light timing, and a Light Regularity
    Index analogous to sleep regularity indices), designed to integrate
    with actigraphy- and sleep-derived circadian metrics from the wider
    Circadia Lab ecosystem.
